                <span class="item-control admin-1585504753 pid-92284639"><a style="border:none;" href="http://www.blogger.com/delete-comment.g?blogID=7336679&amp;postID=112853039703019319" title="Delete Comment" ><span class="delete-comment-icon">&nbsp;</span></a></span>
			</div>
			
			<div class="blogComment">
				&nbsp;<br /><a name="112853112039516040"></a> 
				<I>"no dynamic language of the kind we have right now will save us from failure modes that pertain to the application"</I><BR/><BR/>Erlang is a dynamically type checked language designed for building fault tolerant systems.<BR/><BR/>Here's a good overview <BR/><A HREF="http://www.sics.se/~joe/thesis/armstrong_thesis_2003.pdf" REL="nofollow">Making reliable distributed systems in the presence of software errors</A><BR/><BR/>Here's an industry example<BR/><A HREF="http://www.erlang.se/publications/Ulf_Wiger.pdf" REL="nofollow">Four-fold Increase in Productivity and Quality</A><br />
				<div class="byline">
