                <span class="item-control admin-1585504753 pid-92284639"><a style="border:none;" href="http://www.blogger.com/delete-comment.g?blogID=7336679&amp;postID=112853112039516040" title="Delete Comment" ><span class="delete-comment-icon">&nbsp;</span></a></span>
			</div>
			
			<div class="blogComment">
				&nbsp;<br /><a name="112853677270109266"></a> 
				Isaac, thanks for your comments. <BR/><BR/>Two things.  Yes, it is the default behavior, but I think that play's into Ted's argument that these are dangerous tools for non-experts if put into production settings.<BR/><BR/>With regard to Erlang, I don't think that fits on the roster of what people are promoting as dynamic languages for easy software rolling.  But I think the bigger disconnect is that you and I might not mean the same thing by "application."<BR/><BR/>Is there a better place we could discuss considerations like that?<br />
